  "2026-05-16T14:51:09.488Z",claude-code-agent,"2026-05-16 Audit Session — Full Results:\n\nHEALTH: ok=false (5 history drift hash mismatches from prior redaction — known, tracked in pm-xk39)\nSTORAGE: 710 items, 713 history streams\nITEMS: open=3, in_progress=4, closed=694, canceled=9\nVALIDATION: 27 missing linked paths (legacy src/ moves), 64 orphaned paths (new files) — tracked in pm-xz1p\nTESTS: 1304 tests across 92 files — all passing\n\nSENTRY (unresolved):\n- PM-CLI-Q: localeCompare on undefined (2026-05-14) → FIXED in this session (pm-b9y1)\n- PM-CLI-P: ENOENT lstat race condition (2026-05-11) → FIXED in this session (pm-bh13)\n- PM-CLI-N/H/K/J/M/F/D/G/E: extension activation/run errors (2026-05-10) — environment-specific, scrubbed paths\n- PM-CLI-A/9: Embedding timeout (2026-05-08) — ollama service timeouts, not a code bug\n\nPERFORMANCE (pm-tibg):\n- pm --version: 177ms\n- pm list: 373ms\n- pm context: 569ms\n- pm health (fast): 774ms (new --skip-integrity --skip-drift --skip-vectors)\n- pm health (full): 1.8-7s (cold cache)\n- pm search keyword: 1.1s\n\nGITHUB PRs:\n- PR#22 (pnpm/action-setup): ALL CI FAILURE — do not merge\n- PR#24 (prod deps): ubuntu Node20 FAILURE — investigate before merging\n- PR#26 (dev deps): pnpm-lock.yaml only — review when CI is green\n\nFIXES IMPLEMENTED:\n1. localeCompare defensive ?? '' guards: list.ts, contracts.ts\n2. Extension stat TOCTOU race: extension.ts\n3. Health fast path: --skip-integrity --skip-drift --skip-vectors flags + --full\n4. Health MCP description: documents fast path options\n5. 2 new tests for skip/full flags in health"
close_reason: "Audit complete. Fixed 3 Sentry bugs (PM-CLI-Q localeCompare, PM-CLI-P ENOENT race, health.ts migration comparator). Added health fast-path flags (--skip-integrity/--skip-drift/--skip-vectors/--full) cutting routine health checks from 5-7s to ~800ms. 1306 tests pass. Remaining open items: pm-xk39 (history redaction), pm-xz1p (linked file hygiene), pm-2723 (Dependabot PRs blocked on CI). Committed 3351f84 and pushed to main."
